## Prerequisites

To run this app, you'll need the following installed on your machine:

1. **Node.js**

   - Download and install the latest LTS version from [https://nodejs.org/](https://nodejs.org/). This includes npm, which is required for dependency installation.

2. **Visual Studio Code (optional)**

   - Download and install VS Code from [https://code.visualstudio.com/](https://code.visualstudio.com/). This editor is recommended for its support for extensions and debugging.

3. **Expo CLI**
   - Once Node.js is installed, open a terminal and install the Expo CLI globally by running:
     ```
     npm install -g expo-cli
     ```

## Running the App

1. **Install Dependencies**

   - In the project folder, install all libraries:
     ```
     npm install
     ```

2. **Start the App**

   - To launch the app, run:
     ```
     npm start
     ```

3. **Open the App with Expo Go**
   - Install the **Expo Go** app on your mobile device:
     - [Expo Go on Android](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=host.exp.exponent)
     - [Expo Go on iOS](https://apps.apple.com/us/app/expo-go/id982107779)
   - Open **Expo Go** on your device.
   - Scan the QR code displayed in your terminal or browser after running `npm start` to load the app on your device.

## Build Guide

1. **Create an Expo Account**

   - Sign up at [https://expo.dev/](https://expo.dev/) if you haven't already.

2. **Build with EAS**

   - In the terminal, build an Android preview APK:
     ```
     eas build -p android --profile preview
     ```

3. **Enter Expo Credentials**

   - Log in with your Expo account credentials when prompted.

4. **Download the APK**
   - Once the build completes, download the APK file from the provided link.

---

This guide includes all the steps to get the app running on your device through Expo Go or by building an APK.
